body:
@SteveL-MSFT @mklement0  Since `Clear-Host` on Windows already clears the scrollback buffer, this new switch `-All` would be a useless parameter on Windows resulting in either an error or it being silently ignored if used, neither of which seem undesirable.

> Note: As before, this means that in the Windows console you do not have the option to selectively clear the current screen only, without erasing the scrollback buffer.

We can certainly implement this on Windows if desired, but I don't know that I've ever wanted it. YMMV. 

@JamesWTruher @joeyaiello IIRC, the thrust of what we discussed in the committee meeting is that PowerShell would call `Console.Clear()` on all 'console' platforms and the CoreCLR team would implement the appropriate behaviour on each platform.  If the CoreCLR isn't doing the right thing on a platform, then a bug should be opened in the CoreCLR repo.  ***BUT(!) we do still need to go through the `$Host.UI.RawUI` APIs in order to support 'non-console' platforms like remoting.*** In fact, if the `RawUI` APIs were fully supported on non-Windows console hosts, this whole discussion might be moot.

@mklement0 just to be clear, @PowerShell/powershell-committee decisions aren't and don't have to be unanimous but in the end we have to agree and move on.

One of the arguments presented is that Unix has this current behavior and if significant users wanted the scrollback buffer cleared, then we would have expected `clear` to have changed.    Isn't your CoreFx change to add a parameter to allow clearing the scrollback buffer and not clearing it by default?  In anycase, `Clear-Host` can't use [Console]::Clear() since it doesn't work over PowerShell remoting (unless it solely relied on VT100 and/or printing output...).

Personally, I'll have $PSDefaultParameterValues in my $Profile to cover this...

@SteveL-MSFT If the logic for clear host is moved to `ConsoleHostRawUserInterface.SetBufferContents` then the original function will work remotely.  In [PSES we check](https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShellEditorServices/blob/8730ea45639d20ed63f0ce8a3b12f77b846a35e6/src/PowerShellEditorServices/Session/Host/TerminalPSHostRawUserInterface.cs#L243-L258) for the parameters that the `Clear-Host` function sends:

```csharp
public override void SetBufferContents(
    Rectangle rectangle,
    BufferCell fill)
{
    // If the rectangle is all -1s then it means clear the visible buffer
    if (rectangle.Top == -1 &&
        rectangle.Bottom == -1 &&
        rectangle.Left == -1 &&
        rectangle.Right == -1)
    {
        System.Console.Clear();
        return;
    }


    this.internalRawUI.SetBufferContents(rectangle, fill);
}
```

If similar logic (just now realizing we don't check the fill, that needs to change) is put into `ConsoleHost`, then you could change how `Clear-Host` works without hurting remoting (or other hosts) since `ServerRemoteHost` will send the request back to `ConsoleHost`.
